ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: When did you think it was important to seek help for yourself: More specifically, when did you first notice a change, that something was wrong?
Notes: Date must be completed in form MM/DD/YYYY

When did you think it was important to seek help for yourself: What do you think triggered this?
What, if anything, seemed to aggravate the symptoms?
How did you cope with the symptoms?
Are you currently taking antipsychotic medication?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: If yes, what is the start date of your antipsychotic medication?
Notes: Date must be completed in form MM/DD/YYYY

ElementDescription: Have you taken antipsychotic medication before?
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes

ElementDescription: If yes, what is the start date of your antipsychotic medication prior?
